  "response_text": "Here’s a balanced weekly workout plan designed for **general fitness, fat loss, and muscle tone**. It combines strength training, cardio, and recovery.\n\n*Note: Adjust weights, reps, and intensity based on your current fitness level. Always warm up for 5–10 minutes (e.g., light jog, dynamic stretches) and cool down/stretch afterward.*\n\n---\n\n### Weekly Schedule\n\n| Day | Focus | Example Workout |\n|------|-------|----------------|\n| **Monday** | Full Body Strength (Push Focus) | Squats, Bench Press (or Push-ups), Overhead Press, Plank |\n| **Tuesday** | Low-Intensity Cardio + Core | 30–40 min brisk walk, jog, or cycling + 10 min core work |\n| **Wednesday** | Full Body Strength (Pull Focus) | Deadlifts (or Romanian Deadlifts), Bent-over Rows, Pull-ups (or Lat Pulldowns), Farmer’s Walk |\n| **Thursday** | Active Recovery or Yoga | 20–30 min stretching, foam rolling, or a gentle yoga flow |\n| **Friday** | Full Body Strength (Legs + Power) | Goblet Squats, Lunges, Hip Thrusts, Box Jumps (or Step-ups) |\n| **Saturday** | HIIT + Accessories | 20 min HIIT (e.g., sprint intervals, burpees, jump rope) + 15 min biceps/triceps/shoulders |\n| **Sunday** | Rest or Light Activity | Complete rest, or a long walk, hike, or leisurely swim |\n\n---\n\n### Detailed Workout Examples\n\n**Monday – Push Focus (Full Body)**\n- **Squats:** 3 sets of 8–10 reps\n- **Bench Press (or Push-ups):** 3 sets of 8–12 reps\n- **Overhead Press (Dumbbell or Barbell):** 3 sets of 8–10 reps\n- **Plank:** 3 sets of 30–60 seconds\n\n**Wednesday – Pull Focus (Full Body)**\n- **Deadlifts (or Romanian Deadlifts):** 3 sets of 6–8 reps\n- **Bent-over Rows:** 3 sets of 8–10 reps\n- **Pull-ups (or Lat Pulldowns):** 3 sets of as many reps as possible (AMRAP)\n- **Farmer’s Walk:** 3 sets of 30–45 seconds (heavy dumbbells in each hand)\n\n**Friday – Legs + Power**\n- **Goblet Squats:** 3 sets of 10–12 reps\n- **Walking Lunges:** 3 sets of 10 reps per leg\n- **Hip Thrusts:** 3 sets of 10–12 reps\n- **Box Jumps (or Step-ups):** 3 sets of 6–8 reps (focus on explosive movement)\n\n**Saturday – HIIT + Accessories**\n- **HIIT:** 20 minutes (e.g., 30 sec sprint / 90 sec walk, repeat 8 times)\n- **Bicep Curls:** 3 sets of 12–15 reps\n- **Tricep Dips (or Overhead Extensions):** 3 sets of 10–12 reps\n- **Lateral Raises:** 3 sets of 12–15 reps\n\n---\n\n### Key Principles\n\n- **Progressive Overload:** Each week, try to add a small amount of weight, an extra rep, or one more set.\n- **Rest Between Sets:** 60–90 seconds for strength, 30–60 seconds for HIIT.\n- **Nutrition & Hydration:** Eat enough protein (0.7–1g per pound of bodyweight) and drink water throughout the day.\n- **Listen to Your Body:** If you’re sore or tired, swap a hard day for active recovery. Overtraining leads to injury.\n\n---\n\nWould you like me to adjust this plan for a specific goal (e.g., muscle building, weight loss, home vs. gym), or provide alternative exercises if you don’t have equipment?",
